    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for members of various species of relatively small, short-necked, large-billed waterfowl. They differ from geese in being smaller in size and having legs that are placed rearward, and the result is a distinctive waddling gait. Males, known as drakes, and females, known as hens, exhibit some degree of differentiation in plumage and in call.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
